headlines.description: Matt Morgan scored 21 points, his 12th straight game with at least 20, and Cornell defeated Central Penn 93-69 on Friday.

headlines.description: Lance Tejada made six 3-pointers and scored 25 points and Lehigh rallied from an early 16-point deficit to beat Holy Cross 83-77 on Friday.

headlines.description: Corey Sanders scored 23 points on 10-of-19 shooting to give Rutgers a much-needed win over Wisconsin, 64-60, Friday night.

headlines.description: Kurk Lee scored five of his 22 points in overtime and Alihan Demir finished with a career-high 20 points to help Drexel beat College of Charleston 87-82 on Friday night.

headlines.description: Frederick Scott had a career-high 25 points on Friday night and Rider led by double digits throughout the second half in a 96-77 win over Fairfield.
headlines.shortLinkText: Scott scores career-high 25, Rider beats Fairfield 96-77

headlines.description: Marvin Prochet scored 20 points and grabbed 11 rebounds for his fifth double-double of the season, Matt Scott added 18 points, and Niagara beat Siena 84-76 on Friday night.

headlines.description: Diago Quinn scored a career-high 19 points, Deion Hammond added 17 and Monmouth beat Manhattan 77-66 on Friday night.

headlines.description: Rickey McGill scored 19 points, including nine in a game-ending 25-11 run over the final four minutes as Iona rallied to beat Saint Peter's 73-69 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McGill leads late rally in Iona's 73-69 victory

headlines.description: Nathan Knight had his third consecutive double-double and Matt Milon scored 22 points, including a career-high tying six 3-pointers, to help William & Mary cruise to a 90-65 win over Delaware on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knight, Milon lead William & Mary to 90-65 win over Delaware

headlines.description: Vasa Pusica had four 3-pointers and 20 points on Friday night and Northeastern built a 25-point lead in the first half and then held on to beat Elon 72-60.
headlines.shortLinkText: Northeastern hangs on after big first half, beats Elon 72-60

headlines.description: Justin Wright-Foreman scored 26 points, Rokas Gustys had 12 points and 18 rebounds and Hofstra beat James Madison 87-81 in overtime on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hofstra outlasts James Madison 87-81 in OT

headlines.description: Mike Morsell made four 3-pointers and scored 24 points to help Towson beat defending Colonial Athletic Association champion UNC Wilmington 89-71 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towson beats defending CAA champ UNC Wilmington 89-71

headlines.description: Bryce Dulin hit a career-high seven 3-pointers on eight attempts and finished with 23 points to help Navy beat American 70-64 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dulin hits 8 3s, scores 23 points; Navy beats American 70-64

headlines.description: Stephen Brown had 19 points on 8-of-12 shooting including 3 of 6 from 3-point range to help Bucknell beat Army 83-66 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucknell pulls away early in 2nd half to beat Army 83-66

headlines.description: Andre Walker made four 3-pointers and tied his season high with 27 points to help Loyola beat Boston University 68-65 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Loyola (Md.) beats Boston University 68-65

headlines.description: Justin Jaworski hit a 3-pointer with three seconds left to send Lafayette to a 71-68 victory over Colgate on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaworski's 3-pointer lifts Lafayette to 71-68 triumph

headlines.description: Lamar Stevens set a Bryce Jordan Center record with 14 field goals and scored 16 of a career-high 30 points in the first half to lead Penn State over Northwestern 78-63 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stevens sets BJC record in win over Northwestern

headlines.description: Isaiah Reese scored 20 points, Jermaine Crumpton added 19 and Canisius beat Quinnipiac 82-74 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Canisius beats Quinnipiac 82-74

headlines.description: Grant Benzinger made a career-tying six 3-pointers and scored 23 points and Wright State held off Detroit Mercy for an 80-73 victory on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Benzinger scores 23 points, Wright State wins 80-73

headlines.description: Carson Williams and Lavone Holland II combined to score 24 of their 40 points in the second half and Jordan Garnett had all of his 10 points after the break to help Northern Kentucky rally for an 87-83 win over Oakland on Friday night.

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
